---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const effective = 'June 16, 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — elect-rix.tech"
  description="How elect-rix.tech handles personal information: privacy-by-design, data minimization, no telemetry. PIPEDA-aligned."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-16">
    <header class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        Privacy is not a compliance afterthought — it is a first principle of how we build.
        This policy explains, in plain language, what we collect, why, and what we never do.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-text-muted">Effective date: {effective}</p>
    </header>

    <!-- Summary -->
    <div class="mb-12 p-6 rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-text-muted uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">The short version</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-text-muted list-disc list-inside">
        <li>This website runs <strong class="text-text">no analytics, no trackers, no advertising pixels</strong>.</li>
        <li>We collect personal information <strong class="text-text">only when you choose to contact us</strong>.</li>
        <li>We do not sell, rent, or trade your information. Ever.</li>
        <li>Your data resides in Canada. We minimize what we hold and delete what we no longer need.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Who we are -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">1. Who We Are</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        This website is operated by <strong class="text-text">RixBot Technologies Inc.</strong>, a New Brunswick
        corporation, carrying on business as <strong class="text-text">elect-rix Technology Solutions</strong>
        (the brand "elect-rix"). References to "we", "us", or "our" mean RixBot Technologies Inc. We are a
        Canadian technology consultancy. Our principal place of business is New Brunswick, Canada.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- What we collect -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">2. What We Collect — and What We Don't</h2>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border overflow-hidden mb-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead class="bg-surface-light">
            <tr>
              <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-text">Source</th>
              <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-text">What is collected</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-border">
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Browsing this site</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text-muted">Nothing identifying. No analytics, no cookies for tracking, no fingerprinting. Standard server/CDN request logs may exist transiently at our hosting provider for security and abuse prevention.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Contacting us by email</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text-muted">Your email address and whatever you choose to include in your message (e.g. name, organization, the nature of your inquiry).</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Engaging our services</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text-muted">Information necessary to deliver and invoice the engagement (contact details, scope, and any materials you provide). Handled under the engagement contract and NDA.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        We do <strong class="text-text">not</strong> use third-party advertising networks, behavioural tracking,
        social media tracking pixels, or session-replay tools on this site.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Why -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">3. Why We Collect It (Purpose)</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-text-muted list-disc list-inside">
        <li>To respond to your inquiry and correspond with you.</li>
        <li>To provide, schedule, and invoice services you request.</li>
        <li>To meet legal, accounting, and tax obligations.</li>
        <li>To protect the site and our systems from abuse or attack.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-4 text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        We collect only what is reasonably necessary for these purposes — the principle of
        <strong class="text-text">data minimization</strong>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Email routing -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">4. Email and Hosting Providers</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
        To deliver this website and route email, we rely on third-party infrastructure providers:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-text-muted list-disc list-inside">
        <li><strong class="text-text">Website hosting / CDN:</strong> Cloudflare Pages serves this static site. Cloudflare may process limited request metadata (such as IP address) transiently for delivery and security.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-text">Email routing:</strong> messages to addresses at elect-rix.tech (e.g. hello@, contact@) are routed to our mailbox provider. Treat email as you would any internet email — do not send sensitive credentials or secrets unsolicited.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-4 text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        These providers act on our behalf for the limited purpose of operating the site and email. We do not
        authorize them to use your information for their own marketing.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Retention -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">5. How Long We Keep It</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        We retain personal information only as long as needed for the purpose it was collected, or as required by
        law (for example, tax and accounting records). Inquiry correspondence that does not lead to an engagement is
        deleted once it is no longer useful. Upon completion of an engagement, client data is returned or destroyed
        per the written instruction in the engagement contract.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Disclosure -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">6. When We Disclose Information</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">We do not sell or rent personal information. We disclose it only:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-text-muted list-disc list-inside">
        <li>To service providers strictly necessary to operate (hosting, email, payment/accounting), bound to protect it.</li>
        <li>When required by Canadian law, a court order, or lawful authority.</li>
        <li>With your consent, or as set out in an engagement contract you have signed.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Your rights -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">7. Your Rights</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Under Canada's <strong class="text-text">Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act (PIPEDA)</strong>
        and applicable provincial law, you may:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-text-muted list-disc list-inside">
        <li>Ask what personal information we hold about you and request access to it.</li>
        <li>Request correction of inaccurate information.</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent or ask us to delete information we no longer need.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-4 text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        To exercise any of these, email <a href="mailto:contact@elect-rix.tech" class="text-accent-bright hover:underline">contact@elect-rix.tech</a>.
        We will respond within a reasonable time. If you are not satisfied, you may contact the
        Office of the Privacy Commissioner of Canada.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Security -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">8. Security</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        We apply access control on a need-to-know basis, do not use shared credentials, and keep client work in
        isolated, access-controlled environments. No method of transmission or storage is perfectly secure, but we
        design to collect little so there is little to lose.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Changes -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        We may update this policy as our practices or the law evolve. The effective date above reflects the current
        version. Material changes will be posted on this page.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact -->
    <section class="mb-4 p-6 rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Contact</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        Privacy questions or requests: <a href="mailto:contact@elect-rix.tech" class="text-accent-bright hover:underline">contact@elect-rix.tech</a><br />
        RixBot Technologies Inc. (operating as elect-rix Technology Solutions), New Brunswick, Canada.
      </p>
    </section>

    <p class="text-center text-sm text-text-muted font-medium pt-8">
      elect-rix.tech &#x2014; Integrity. Loyalty. Honesty. &#x2014; Tested.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
